eraction becomes more frequent, actually hunts with some softskins. Sees more admirable examples of all races, as well as the vile disgusting softskins who are spoken of by the Elders. Wonders at the dichotomy. First stirrings of pity for these less than Iksar beings.<br><br>Forms a guild with some friends, who bring along some non-Iksar &quot;friends&quot; of theirs... a disturbing concept, but his friends are Iksar, so to be trusted.<br><br>Meets a curious Human who sometimes claims to be an Iksar, trapped in the body of a human, sometimes claims to be Karana's Cleric to the Iksar, sent to convert the Empire. Obviously insane, but with some small talent as a healer.<br><br>Meets an Iksar who claims to be a Goblin, in the guise of an Iksar. Obviously insane, perhaps addled as an egg. She shows great prowess as a priestess, first true non-creche friend.<br><br>For a long period, hunting and training far from home, has little interaction with Iksar. Forced to interact more with the softskins, decides since they are to be slaves, they can be used, but sees more and more that is worthy of respect in some. Learns many tongues, masters a few. Truely begins to wonder at the dictates of his Elders. Comes to befriend some of these non-Iksar, long period of confusion.<br><br>Spends much time hunting alone, both near to home and far afield. Spends much time thinking about the Empire, and the softskins. Does not so much have an epiphany, as reaches a conclusion:<br><br>Still numbers many not of the Empire as friends, but realizes that the vision of the Elders is right, even his friends must one day be slaves to the Empire. But also believes the Elders are wrong, slaves can contribute to the Empire, they are like any other possession, some are useful, to be cherished, others not so useful, to be used up.<br><br>Sees no contridiction, other than with the beliefs of his fellow Iksar. Still seeks to solve this contradiction, as he is viewed as less than whole by many within the Empire, but still believes there is some worth in some non-Iksar.<br><br>Xethux<br><br><br><br> <p>Confrontation is the essence of nature, confrontation is the rythm of life. In nature violence is pure and purposeful, one species against another an an act of survival.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usarhea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarhea</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tu'Rilthiil Bladedancer<br>Mod out of retirement!</span><br>  Posts: 1555<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/20/02 11:39:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2741.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/sar.gif width=52 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Xethux tail</span><hr size=1> Sar was born in...well, she grew up in Qeynos, only knowing her father, a Knight of Thunder who worked for Antonious Bayle, guarding the city.  <br><br>As a youngster, she was drawn to the ways of Karana by her father, and sought training with Te'Anara in Surefall Glade.  <br><br>In her 10th season as a druid of Karana, the undead invaded Qeynos Hills, and in battle Sarhea fell, but rather than returning right back to Qeynos, she awoke in a place of mists and thunder, and heard the voice of Karana, who basically told her(the story is on my board) that she was better suited to be a fighter for the Rain, and when she awoke, once again in Surefall, Te'Anara told her that Hager Sureshot would teach her henceforth. <br><br> During this time,